                  </persName>
            . I found he had taken 2s. 6d. at one place, and that I said I would make a debt of, if he would never do the like again - I said nothing about the other money.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18291029-177-person1406">
                  JOHN 
                  ALLEN
               <interp inst="t18291029-177-person1406" type="surname" value="ALLEN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18291029-177-person1406" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18291029-177-person1406" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a coal-dealer, and live in Cow-cross. The prisoner lived nine months with me, and bore a good character; he came to my service again after he left the prosecutor; I took him to Hatton-garden - there was only one charge against him, which the Magistrate would not enter upon; I bailed him: the prosecutor then<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182910290061"></xptr>brought this charge, and told me he would prosecute him if he came into my service, but if he kept out of the way he would not, I will take him into my service now.</p>
